==English==
===Pronunciation===
*tīd'əl wāv, /ˈtaɪdəl weɪv/, /<tt>"taId@l weIv</tt>/

===Noun===
'''[[tidal]] [[wave]]''' ([[tidal waves]])

#A crest of ocean water resulting from tidal forces.
#A [[tsunami]]. A very large [[wave]], caused by a tremendous disturbance in the ocean, such as an [[undersea]] [[earthquake]] or volcanic eruption, that often causes colossal damage when it reaches land.
#: ''Note: this sense of ''tidal wave'' is frequently discouraged, because these waves are completely unrelated to tidal forces.  Tsunami is generally used instead.''

